  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A literature-review activity was used to satisfy the output-comparison requirement; the requirement binding specifies experimental-validation as the required verification method, but the supporting activity is a literature-review, creating an inference method mismatch (W-AR-03). The narrative describes the literature sources as complementary benchmarks, but the structured activityType disagrees with the requiredVerificationMethod.",
