    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessor",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the package based on the literature-review comparison activity, which was judged to provide adequate benchmark coverage for the output comparison factor. The Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification results demonstrated that 95th-percentile hemolysis predictions remain below the clinical threshold across all five operating points. The team noted that the literature sources span a range of centrifugal pump geometries and operating conditions that collectively bound the VAD COU envelope. No experimental campaign was deemed necessary given the breadth of published data. All seven assessed credibility factors were reviewed; six factors remain as epistemic gaps but were scoped as acceptable at this stage of development. Decision: Accepted pending resolution of epistemic gaps in subsequent design verification phase.",
